# ⚙️ 5️⃣ What is CI/CD?

🔥 Very commonly asked

---

## CI = Continuous Integration

Whenever developers push code:

```text
Code
 ↓
Automatic Testing
```

---

### Why?

Catch bugs early.

---

## CD = Continuous Deployment

If tests pass:

```text
Code
 ↓
Deploy Automatically
```

---

### Mental Model 🚗

Factory Assembly Line

Code enters one side.

Working software comes out.

---

### Benefits

✅ Faster releases

✅ Fewer bugs

✅ Automation

---

### Interview Gold Line ⭐

"CI/CD automates testing and deployment, allowing teams to release software quickly and reliably."

---

# ⚙️ 6️⃣ Why Companies Use CI/CD

Without CI/CD:

```text
Developer
 ↓
Manual Testing
 ↓
Manual Deployment
```

Slow and error-prone.

---

With CI/CD:

```text
Developer
 ↓
Push Code
 ↓
Pipeline
 ↓
Testing
 ↓
Deployment
```

Automatic.

